A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act creating the State Court of Cobb County, approved March 26, 1964 (Ga. L.
2 1964, p. 3211), as amended, so as to change the compensation and number of certain staff
3 of the solicitor-general; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for
4 other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 An Act creating the State Court of Cobb County, approved March 26, 1964 (Ga. L. 1964,
8 p. 3211), as amended, particularly by an Act approved May 12, 2008 (Ga. L. 2008, p. 3723),
9 and an Act approved May 12, 2015 (Ga. L. 2015, p. 4059), is amended by revising paragraph
10 (1) of subsection (d) of Section 27 as follows:
11 "(d)(1) The solicitor-general shall have the authority to appoint two assistant solicitors
12 for each judge of Division I and Division II of the State Court of Cobb County and the
13 same number of additional assistant solicitors as the number of full-time magistrates of
14 the Magistrate Court of Cobb County, plus six additional assistant solicitors, one of
15 whom shall be the chief assistant solicitor, four of whom may be deputy assistant
16 solicitors, and one of whom may serve as an intake attorney at the Cobb County Adult
